snippet.textDisplay:
I'm new to this channel. Here are my thoughts:


Why are you such a dick in this video? Look at the like-to-dislike ratio on this video and have a hard reflection about whether this is what you want. You use the emphatic-pause-then-call-it-"unique" routine so much it makes me cringe. You think you're cool and intelligent by belittling the controller in this way, but the paradoxical thing is that your reliance on this crutch makes you appear both boring and dumb, and does nothing to build an audience that respects you.


I watched the video because I was interested in the features of the new controller and was looking forward to making my own opinions about it based on your expert analysis of performance and key features, etc.; however, you just kept inserting your stupid commentary at points where an actual expert analysis would have been far more useful. Please, just review it in an unbiased way! For example, when you compared the ps5 to the xbox series x and hypothesized performance differences, that was far more interesting commentary. Additionally, if you can back such hypotheses up with evidence that makes you an "expert", you are giving new viewers a reason to come to your channel specifically.


As it stands, you took an angle on this video that undermined your own good qualities, and made you come across as an obnoxious a-hole (even though I know you're probably not). It doesn't make me want to watch any more of your videos, even if the titles indicate content I'm interested in.

snippet.textDisplay:
The problem that no one acknowledges with Xbox One controllers is you’re forced to buy the rechargeable battery add on, which unnecessarily adds to the cost of the controller. If they were smart, they’d include a removable rechargeable battery back, also allowing the option for AA batteries for those who prefer that. Or at least make the price lower. But Instead, they charge the same price as the PS4 controller , which offers waaayy more features , such as the internal battery, light bar, speaker, gyro motion sensor, and a touch pad. (Current price for PS4 and XB1 controllers are $45)
I mean, you can’t deny the value. MS overcharges. Point blank period.
I’m still getting both consoles. But I do think MS is being selfish to continue their trend of forcing ppl to buy an add-on just to have the rechargeable option. When 99% of modern electronics have lithium ion rechargeable batteries.
And I bet the price won’t be any less than Sony’s will be for their PS5 controllers. It’s just obvious which company truly goes for value and who doesn’t.
